article.headline: Texas-Pan American 67, CS Bakersfield 60
article.story: BAKERSFIELD, Calif. (AP) -- Paul Stoll scored 15 of his 20 points in the second half to lead Texas-Pan American to a 67-60 victory Friday night over Cal State Bakersfield. Zach Trader and Emmanuel Jones added 17 points apiece for the Broncs (17-13), who trailed by a point at halftime before Stoll's charge, and led by as many as 10 in the second half. Donovan Bragg scored 19 for Cal State Bakersfield (8-19) and Terrence Johns scored 14. The Broncs shot 46 percent from the field to the Roadrunners' 40 percent. Texas-Pan American beat Bakersfield handily, 86-68, 10 days earlier in Edinburg, Texas.
